  "prompt": "Can someone get two graduation degree at same time?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to earn two graduation degrees simultaneously, though the specific approach can vary:\n\n1. Double Major:\n- Complete two different majors within the same degree program\n- Earn one degree with two specializations\n- Usually takes the same time as a single major\n\n2. Dual Degree Programs:\n- Earn two separate degrees from the same or different universities\n- Can be in different disciplines\n- Often requires additional time and credits\n- Examples: Bachelor of Arts and Bachelor of Science\n\n3. Concurrent Degree Programs:\n- Pursue two different degrees simultaneously\n- Might require more credit hours\n- Can be completed in less time than pursuing degrees sequentially\n\n4. Online/Flexible Learning:\n- Some universities offer flexible programs allowing simultaneous degree pursuit\n- Distance learning can make this easier\n\n5. International Options:\n- Some universities offer joint or collaborative degree programs\n- Students can earn degrees from multiple institutions\n\nConsiderations:\n- Higher workload\n- Additional academic requirements\n- Potential extra costs\n- More time commitment\n- Specific university policies\n\nThe feasibility depends on the specific university, program structure, and individual academic capabilities.",
